{
  "schema_version": "GOLD_ENGINE_COMMANDS_FULL_V1_4_14",
  "description": "Gold v1.4.14. Bumps two engine versions per the live session-quality-audit remediation (GOLD_PIPELINE_SPEC_V3_TASK_RELEVANCE.md Section 2.4, GOLD_PIPELINE_SPEC_V5_AUDIT_REMEDIATION.md Findings 3-4), written as new versioned files rather than edits to the v1.4.13-referenced originals: 'evaluator' now runs va_premium_evaluator_v8_4_wke_standalone.py (was v8_3) -- fixes arg_claim_relevance/maintain_task_focus never checking the essay against the assigned prompt, by threading prompt_text into the LLM refinement payload and lowering their heuristic ceilings from DEPTH_2 to DEPTH_1. 'lret_session' now runs lret_engine_v1_12_1_meaning_sensitive_detector_families.py (was v1_12_0) -- fixes find_covering_task_for_keep()/covers_unit() failing to recognize a KEEP candidate and a FIX unit as the same underlying span when their source_sentence_index values disagreed (the 'sound mental' appearing in both fix_units and keep_units bug). Full Gold v1.4.13 command config. Fixes stress-test Problem 2 (found via a weak/medium/strong 3-essay stress test): the scorer's task_response/coherence_cohesion content-quality sub-metrics were never populated by anything upstream and sat at a hardcoded 0.55 default on every run regardless of essay content. 'evaluator' now runs BEFORE 'scorer' (previously after score_contract/progress_tracker); its --scorer input is now omitted since no scorer artifact exists yet at that point (the underlying evaluator engine already has a graceful scorer_available=False fallback for this). A new 'evaluator_rubric_bridge' stage (evaluator_rubric_bridge_v1.py) maps the Evaluator's skill_observation_profile into scorer-readable TR/CC fields, merged with any real signal det_vip's own detector_metric_profile already carries. 'scorer' now reads {evaluator_rubric_bridge} instead of {detector_for_scorer} directly. Verified locally against real weak/medium/strong stress-test data: task_response raw_quality went from bit-for-bit identical (0.558/0.558/0.558) to differentiated (0.528/0.565/0.643, monotonic with essay quality) before this fix was even wired into a live run.",
